{"title_page": "Barn Coppice", "text_new": "{{infobox park\n| name = Barn Coppice\n| photo = Barn Coppice, Graylands Horsham. Woodland scene.jpg\n| photo_caption =\n| type = Ancient woodland\n| grid_ref_UK =  TQ177339\n| location =   Graylands Horsham, England\n| area =    0.01 sq mi (0.01 km\u00b2)\n}}\n\n'''Barn Coppice''' is an [[ancient woodland]] in [[Graylands]], a hamlet close to [[Horsham]], [[England]]. It lies on the flat southern expanse of the hamlet, in-between a scrubland and a field, 300 meters (993 ft) north of the [[A264]] dual carriageway. \n\nThe woodland defined by a low woodbank on three sides, with an inaccessible southern edge. The interior is very irregular, with a large waterfilled pit in the centre and numerous other small pits scattered throughout. The presence of the pits is evidence of the historical quarrying of [[Horsham Stone]]. <ref>https://northhorsham.files.wordpress.com/2018/09/ase-heritage-statement.pdf p.23</ref>\n\nOld brick footings are visible in the south-east corner of the woodland. These remnants relate to agricultural buildings that existed on the site from at least the 1840s. <ref>https://northhorsham.files.wordpress.com/2018/09/ase-heritage-statement.pdf p.98 Horsham tithe map, 1844 (south-west) </ref>\n\n== Gallery ==\n<gallery mode=\"packed\" heights=\"180px\">\nFile:Barn Coppice, Graylands Horsham. Pond 02.jpg|This large water-filled pit is the the dominant feature of the woodland.\nFile:Barn Coppice, Graylands Horsham. Pond.jpg|The Barn Coppice water pit is largely stagnant and plagued with [[pond scum]].\nFile:Barn Coppice, Graylands Horsham. Brick footing.jpg|Evidence of brick footings from the mid-19th century indicated agricultural activity nearby.\n</gallery>\n\n== References ==\n\n\n[[Category:Forests and woodlands of West Sussex]]\n\n{{WestSussex-geo-stub}}\n\n== References ==\n", "text_old": "{{infobox park\n| name = Barn Coppice\n| photo = Barn Coppice, Graylands Horsham. Woodland scene.jpg\n| photo_caption =\n| type = Ancient woodland\n| grid_ref_UK =  TQ177339\n| location =   Graylands Horsham, England\n| area =    0.01 sq mi (0.01 km\u00b2)\n}}\n\n'''Barn Coppice''' is an [[ancient woodland]] in [[Graylands]], a hamlet close to [[Horsham]], [[England]]. It lies on the flat southern expanse of the hamlet, in-between a scrubland and field, 300 meters (993 ft) north of the [[A264]] dual carriageway. \n\nThe woodland defined by a low woodbank on three sides, with an inaccessible southern edge. The interior is very irregular, with a large waterfilled pit in the centre and numerous other small pits scattered throughout. The presence of the pits is evidence of the historical quarrying of [[Horsham Stone]]. <ref>https://northhorsham.files.wordpress.com/2018/09/ase-heritage-statement.pdf p.23</ref>\n\nOld brick footings are visible in the south-east corner of the woodland. These remnants relate to agricultural buildings that existed on the site from at least the 1840s. <ref>https://northhorsham.files.wordpress.com/2018/09/ase-heritage-statement.pdf p.98 Horsham tithe map, 1844 (south-west) </ref>\n\n== Gallery ==\n<gallery mode=\"packed\" heights=\"180px\">\nFile:Barn Coppice, Graylands Horsham. Pond 02.jpg|This large water-filled pit is the the dominant feature of the woodland.\nFile:Barn Coppice, Graylands Horsham. Pond.jpg|The Barn Coppice water pit is largely stagnant and plagued with [[pond scum]].\nFile:Barn Coppice, Graylands Horsham. Brick footing.jpg|Evidence of brick footings from the mid-19th century indicated agricultural activity nearby.\n</gallery>\n\n== References ==\n\n\n[[Category:Forests and woodlands of West Sussex]]\n\n{{WestSussex-geo-stub}}\n\n== References ==\n", "name_user": "Poleg\u00e5arden", "label": "safe", "comment": "a. minor typo", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barn_Coppice"}
{"title_page": "G\u00fcm\u00fc\u015fl\u00fck International Classical Music Festival", "text_new": "{{underlinked|date=April 2019}}\n\nThe '''G\u00fcm\u00fc\u015fl\u00fck International Classical Music Festival''' is held in the small fishing village of [[G\u00fcm\u00fc\u015fl\u00fck]], [[Bodrum]], on the southwest coast of [[Turkey]]. It began in 2004 and between 2006 and 2012 was organized by ''Bodrum Klasik M\u00fczik Derne\u011fi'' (Classical Music Association of Bodrum), founded in 2006 for this purpose.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.annalindhfoundation.org/members/bodrum-klasik-muzik-dernegi|title=Bodrum Klasik Muzik Dernegi - Anna Lindh Foundation|website=www.annalindhfoundation.org}}</ref> In 2016 the festival expanded its programming to include a dedicated guitar week and a series of jazz concerts. The G\u00fcm\u00fc\u015fl\u00fck Festival Academy is organized annually parallel to the festival.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gumuslukfestival.org/gfa-akademi|title=GFA AKADEM\u0130 \u2013 Uluslararas\u0131 G\u00fcm\u00fc\u015fl\u00fck Klasik M\u00fczik Festivali|website=www.gumuslukfestival.org}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.gumuslukfestival.org Festival website]\n* [http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/classical-music-days-continue-in-gumusluk-.aspx?pageID=238&nID=85483&NewsCatID=383 Festival 2015 at the Turkish Daily News]\n* [http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/classical-music-to-echo-in-gumusluk.aspx?pageID=238&nID=68942&NewsCatID=383 Festival 2014 at the Turkish Daily News]\n* [http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/Default.aspx?pageID=238&nid=24919 Festival 2012 at the Turkish Daily News]\n\n{{coord missing|Turkey}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Gumusluk International Classical Music Festival}}\n[[Category:Classical music festivals in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Music festivals established in 2004]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Mu\u011fla Province]]\n[[Category:Annual events in Turkey]]\n[[Category:2004 establishments in Turkey]]\n\n\n{{