{"title_page": "2018 Utah Utes football team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n  |sport             = football\n  |year              = 2018\n  |team              = Utah Utes\n  |image             = Utah Utes logo.svg\n  |image_size        = 125\n  |conference        = Pac-12 Conference\n  |division          = South Division\n  |short_conf        = Pac-12\n  |record            = 9\u20135\n  |conf_record       = 6\u20133\n  |head_coach         = [[Kyle Whittingham]]\n  |hc_year            = 14th\n  |off_coach          = [[Troy Taylor (American football)|Troy Taylor]]\n  |oc_year            = 2nd\n  |def_coach          = Morgan Scalley\n  |dc_year            = 3rd\n  |off_scheme           = Multiple\n  |def_scheme           = [[4\u20133 defense|4\u20133]]\n  |stadium      = [[Rice\u2013Eccles Stadium]]<br />(Capacity: 45,807)<ref>[http://stadium.utah.edu/about/stadium/ Rice-Eccles Stadium]. The University of Utah. Retrieved April 19, 2017.</ref>\n  |uniform           = \n  |champion          = Pac-12 South Division champion\n  |conf_champ         = [[2018 Pac-12 Football Championship Game|Pac-12 Championship Game]]\n  |conf_champ_result   = <br>L 3\u201310 vs. [[2018 Washington Huskies football team|Washington]]\n  |bowl              = [[2018 Holiday Bowl|Holiday Bowl]]\n  |bowl_result       = L 20\u201331 vs. [[2018 Northwestern Wildcats football team|Northwestern]]\n}}\n{{2018 Pac-12 football standings}}\nThe '''2018 Utah Utes football team''' represented the [[University of Utah]] during the [[2018 NCAA Division I FBS football season]]. The Utes were led by 14th-year head coach [[Kyle Whittingham]] and played their home games in [[Rice\u2013Eccles Stadium]] in [[Salt Lake City, Utah|Salt Lake City, UT]]. They were members of the South Division of the [[Pac-12 Conference]].\n\nThe Utes completed the regular season with a 6\u20133 record in conference play, winning the South Division for the first time since joining the Pac-12 Conference in [[2011 Utah Utes football team|2011]]. In the [[2018 Pac-12 Football Championship Game|Pac-12 Championship Game]], the team lost to North Division champion [[2018 Washington Huskies football team|Washington]] by a score of 10\u20133. They were invited to the [[2018 Holiday Bowl|Holiday Bowl]] to play [[2018 Big Ten Conference football season|Big Ten Conference]] runner-up [[2018 Northwestern Wildcats football team|Northwestern]], where the Utes lost by a score of 31\u201320 to end the year at 9\u20135 overall.\n\nUtah was led on offense by quarterback [[Tyler Huntley]] until he suffered a season-ending collarbone fracture in the game against [[2018 Arizona State Sun Devils football team|Arizona State]] on November 3. Redshirt freshman Jason Shelley started for the rest of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sltrib.com/sports/utah-utes/2018/11/05/utes-qb-tyler-huntley/|title=Utes QB Tyler Huntley officially is out for the season, but he may play in a bowl game|first=Kurt|last=Kragthorpe|date=November 5, 2018|newspaper=The Salt Lake Tribune}}</ref> Running back [[Zack Moss]] compiled 1,096 rushing yards and 11 touchdowns. Two members of the Utah offensive line earned first-team all-conference honors, Jordan Agasiva and [[Jackson Barton]]. Utah's defense featured four members of the first-team All-Pac-12: defensive linemen [[Bradlee Anae]] and [[Leki Fotu]], linebacker Chase Hansen, and cornerback [[Jaylon Johnson]]. Hansen led the conference in tackles for loss with 22, and Anae tied for the conference lead in sacks with 8.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/conferences/pac-12/2018.html|title=2018 Pacific-12 Conference Year Summary|website=Sports-Reference.com|access-date=June 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Previous season==\nThe Utes finished the [[2017 Utah Utes football team|2017 season]] 7\u20136, 3\u20136 in Pac-12 play to finish in fifth place in the South Division. They were invited to the [[2017 Heart of Dallas Bowl|Heart of Dallas Bowl]] where they defeated [[2017 West Virginia Mountaineers football team|West Virginia]].\n\n==Preseason==\n\n===Position key===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|[[Running back|Back]]\n|'''B'''\n|rowSpan=\"6\" style=\"background-color:lightgrey;\"|\n|[[Center (American football)|Center]]\n|'''C'''\n|rowSpan=\"6\" style=\"background-color:lightgrey;\"|\n|[[Cornerback]]\n|'''CB'''\n|rowSpan=\"6\" style=\"background-color:lightgrey;\"|\n|[[Defensive back]]\n|'''DB'''\n|-\n|[[Defensive end]]\n|'''DE'''\n|[[Defensive lineman]]\n|'''DL'''\n|[[Defensive tackle]]\n|'''DT'''\n|[[End (American football)|End]]\n|'''E'''\n|-\n|[[Fullback (American football)|Fullback]]\n|'''FB'''\n|[[Guard (American football)|Guard]]\n|'''G'''\n|[[Halfback (American football)|Halfback]]\n|'''HB'''\n|[[Placekicker|Kicker]]\n|'''K'''\n|-\n|[[Kickoff returner]]\n|'''KR'''\n|[[Offensive tackle]]\n|'''OT'''\n|[[Lineman (American football)|Offensive lineman]]\n|'''OL'''\n|[[Linebacker]]\n|'''LB'''\n|-\n|[[Long snapper]]\n|'''LS'''\n|[[Punter (American football)|Punter]]\n|'''P'''\n|[[Punt returner]]\n|'''PR'''\n|[[Quarterback]]\n|'''QB'''\n|-\n|[[Running back]]\n|'''RB'''\n|[[Safety (American and Canadian football position)|Safety]]\n|'''S'''\n|[[Tight end]]\n|'''TE'''\n|[[Wide receiver]]\n|'''WR'''\n|}\n\n===Recruits===\nThe Utes signed a total of 20 recruits.\n{{College Athlete Recruit Start|40=no|collapse=yes|year=2018}}\n{{College Athlete Recruit Entry\n| recruit  = Hunter Lotulelei\n| position = OG\n| hometown = [[Salt Lake City, Utah]]\n| highschool = [[Highland High School (Utah)|Highland High School]]\n| feet   = 6\n| inches = 2\n| weight = 213\n| commitdate = June 17, 2016\n| scout stars  = 3\n| rivals stars = 4\n| 247 stars = 3\n| espn stars = 3\n}}\n{{College Athlete Recruit Entry\n| recruit  = Jack Tuttle\n| position = QB\n| hometown = [[San Marcos, California]]\n| highschool = [[Mission Hills High School]]\n| feet   = 6\n| inches = 4\n| weight = 195\n| commitda