l|url=http://pac-12.com/article/2018/07/25/washington-picked-pac-12-favorite-media-preseason-poll/news/?article_id=100|date=July 25, 2018|accessdate=July 25, 2018}}{{Dead link|date=September 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n|align=\"center\" Colspan=\"3\" |'''Media poll (South)'''\n|- align=\"center\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Utah Utes|Predicted finish|Team|Votes (1st place)}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 1 || USC || 225 (22)\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 2 || '''Utah''' || 209 (14)\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 3 || Arizona || 178 (3)\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 4 || UCLA || 116 (2)\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 5 || Colorado || 80 (1)\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 6 || Arizona State || 72 \n|}\n\n==Schedule==\nUtah announced their 2018 football schedule on November 16, 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.deseretnews.com/article/865692855/Utahs-2018-football-schedule-released-by-Pac-12-Utes-to-face-BYU-last-week-of-season.html|title=Utah's 2018 football schedule released by Pac-12; Utes to face BYU last week of season|last=Facer|first=Dirk|date=November 16, 2017 |website=DeseretNews.com|access-date=December 4, 2017}}</ref> The Utes will play [[NCAA Division I Football Championship|FCS]] [[Weber State Wildcats football|Weber State]] and [[Northern Illinois Huskies football|Northern Illinois]] and returning to the traditional last game of the year spot, Utah will play in-state rival [[BYU Cougars football]] in out-of-conference play. In Pac-12 conference play, the Utes will not play cross-divisional foes [[California Golden Bears football|California]] and [[Oregon State Beavers football|Oregon State]].\n\n{{CFB schedule\n| opprank = y\n| rankyear = 2018\n| rankdivision = NCAA Division I FBS\n| poll = AP\n| timezone = Mountain\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = {{tooltip|August 30|Thursday}}\n| time = 6:00 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| opponent = [[2018 Weber State Wildcats football team|Weber State]]\n| opprank = 8 <sm