 days are set for July 25, 2018 in [[Hollywood, California]]. [[Kyle Whittingham]] (HC), Chase Hanson (LB) & Lo Falemaka (OL) at Pac-12 Media Days. The Pac-12 media poll was released with the Utes predicted to finish in second place at Pac-12 South division.<ref>{{cite web|title=Washington picked as Pac-12 favorite in preseason media poll|url=http://pac-12.com/article/2018/07/25/washington-picked-pac-12-favorite-media-preseason-poll/news/?article_id=100|date=July 25, 2018|accessdate=July 25, 2018}}{{Dead link|date=September 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- align=\"center\"\n|align=\"center\" Colspan=\"3\" |'''Media poll (South)'''\n|- align=\"center\"\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Utah Utes|Predicted finish|Team|Votes (1st place)}}\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 1 || USC || 225 (22)\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 2 || '''Utah''' || 209 (14)\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 3 || Arizona || 178 (3)\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 4 || UCLA || 116 (2)\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 5 || Colorado || 80 (1)\n|- align=\"center\"\n| 6 || Arizona State || 72 \n|}\n\n==Schedule==\nUtah announced their 2018 football schedule on November 16, 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.deseretnews.com/article/865692855/Utahs-2018-football-schedule-released-by-Pac-12-Utes-to-face-BYU-last-week-of-season.html|title=Utah's 2018 football schedule released by Pac-12; Utes to face BYU last week of season|last=Facer|first=Dirk|date=November 16, 2017 |website=DeseretNews.com|access-date=December 4, 2017}}</ref> The Utes will play [[NCAA Division I Football Championship|FCS]] [[Weber State Wildcats football|Weber State]] and [[Northern Illinois Huskies football|Northern Illinois]] and returning to the traditional last game of the year spot, Utah will play in-state rival [[BYU Cougars football]] in out-of-conference play. In Pac-12 conference play, the Utes will not play cross-divisional foes [[California Golden Bears football|California]] and [[Oregon State Beavers football|Oregon State]].\n\n{{CFB schedule\n| opprank = y\n| rankyear = 2018\n| rankdivision = NCAA Division I FBS\n| poll = AP\n| timezone = Mountain\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = {{tooltip|August 30|Thursday}}\n| time = 6:00 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| opponent = [[2018 Weber State Wildcats football team|Weber State]]\n| opprank = 8 <small>[[2018 NCAA Division I FCS football season|(FCS)]]</small>\n| site_stadium = [[Rice\u2013Eccles Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Salt Lake City|Salt Lake City, UT]]\n| tv = [[Pac-12 Network|P12N]]\n| score = 41\u201310\n| attend = 45,988\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 8\n| time = 5:30 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| away = y\n| opponent = [[2018 Northern Illinois Huskies football team|Northern Illinois]]\n| site_stadium = [[Huskie Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[DeKalb, Illinois|DeKalb, IL]]\n| tv = [[ESPNews]]\n| score = 17\u20136\n| attend = 16,762\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 15\n| time = 8:00 p.m.\n| w/l = l\n| opponent = [[2018 Washington Huskies football team|Washington]]\n| opprank = 10\n| site_stadium = Rice\u2013Eccles Stadium\n| site_cityst = Salt Lake City, UT\n| tv = [[ESPN College Football Saturday Primetime|ESPN]]\n| score = 7\u201321\n| attend = 47,445\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 29\n| time = 4:00 p.m.\n| w/l = l\n| away = y\n| opponent = [[2018 Washington State Cougars football team|Washington State]]\n| site_stadium = [[Martin Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Pullman, Washington|Pullman, WA]]\n| tv = P12N\n| score = 24\u201328\n| attend = 30,088\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 6\n| time = 8:30 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| away = y\n| opponent = [[2018 Stanford Cardinal football team|Stanford]]\n| opprank = 14\n| site_stadium = [[Stanford Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Stanford, California|Stanford, CA]]\n| tv = ESPN\n| score = 40\u201321\n| attend = 37,244\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = {{tooltip|October 12|Friday}}\n| time = 8:00 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| opponent = [[